    • Method Detail

      • getBattery

        public void getBattery()
        Get the Bp3l battery status
        • This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately.
        • If get device's battery successfully. following callback will be triggered:
          iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
          • The action is BpProfile.ACTION_BATTERY_BP
          • The keys of the message will show in keyList of the action.
        • If error happens, following callback will be triggered:
          iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
          • The action is BpProfile.ACTION_ERROR_BP.
          • The message will be a JSON string with error ID and description,
            the keys will show in the KeyList of the action.
        • Attention, it is mandatory to call following method before you call this method:
          iHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(iHealthDevicesCallback)

      • startMeasure

        public void startMeasure()
        Start On-line measurement.

        • This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately.
        • If start On-line measurement successfully, following callback will be triggered:
          iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
          • The list of actions is
            1. BpProfile.ACTION_ZOREING_BP
            2. BpProfile.ACTION_ZOREOVER_BP
            3. BpProfile.ACTION_ONLINE_PRESSURE_BP
            4. BpProfile.ACTION_ONLINE_PULSEWAVE_BP
            5. BpProfile.ACTION_ONLINE_RESULT_BP
          • The keys of the message will show in BpProfile.ACTION_ZOREING_BP, BpProfile.ACTION_ZOREOVER_BP, BpProfile.ACTION_ONLINE_PRESSURE_BP, BpProfile.ACTION_ONLINE_PULSEWAVE_BP and BpProfile.ACTION_ONLINE_RESULT_BP.

        • If error happens, following callback will be triggered:
          iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
          • The action is BpProfile.ACTION_ERROR_BP.
          • The message will be a JSON string with error ID and description,
            the keys will show in the KeyList of the action.
        • Attention, it is mandatory to call following method before you call this method:
          iHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(iHealthDevicesCallback)

      • interruptMeasure

        public void interruptMeasure()
        Interrupt the measuring process immediately if device is in measuring state.
        • This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately.
        • If interrupt the measuring process successfully, following callback will be triggered:
          iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
          • The action is BpProfile.ACTION_INTERRUPTED_BP.
          • The message is null.

        • If error happens, following callback will be triggered:
          iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
          • The action is BpProfile.ACTION_ERROR_BP.
          • The message will be a JSON string with error ID and description,
            the keys will show in the KeyList of the action.
        • Attention, it is mandatory to call following method before you call this method:
          iHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(iHealthDevicesCallback)

      • disconnect

        public void disconnect()
        Disconnect the Bp3l.
        • This is an asynchronous call, it will return immediately.
        • If disconnect device successfully, following callback will be triggered:
          iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceConnectionStateChange(String mac, String deviceType, int status, int errorID, Map manufactorData)
          • The status is iHealthDevicesManager.DEVICE_STATE_DISCONNECTED.
        • If error happens, following callback will be triggered:
          iHealthDevicesCallback.onDeviceNotify(String mac, String deviceType, String action, String message)
          • The action is BpProfile.ACTION_ERROR_BP.
          • The message will be a JSON string with error ID and description,
            the keys will show in the KeyList of the action.
        • Attention, it is mandatory to call following method before you call this method:
          iHealthDevicesManager.registerClientCallback(iHealthDevicesCallback)
        Specified by:
        disconnect in interface DeviceControl
